Important!!!

You should follow the instructions below now, just to avoid confusion!

##############################################
# MAKE PAPERWORLD3D TRUSTED
##############################################

in order to run paperworld3d locally you'll need to place the 'paperworld.cfg' file in the flashplayertrust directory

On Windows
____________________________________________________
C:\Windows\System32\Macromed\Flash\FlashPlayerTrust
____________________________________________________

and the edit the path in the file - make it the path to the directory this README file is in right now!

If you don't do this you won't be able to run paperworld3d locally because of FP9's security settings.

##############################################
# EDIT YOUR USER PROPERTIES	
##############################################

Open up the user.properties file in the src/build directory 

Edit the FLEX_HOME property to point to the location of the Flex SDK on your system

Edit the RED5_HOME property to point to the location of Red5 on your system.